\section mdspan

Polymorphic Multidimensional Array Reference,
http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2018/p0009r5.html. The
proposed polymorphic multidimensional array reference (mdspan) defines types and
functions for mapping indices from a multidimensional index space (the domain)
to members of a contiguous span of objects (the codomain). A multidimensional
index space is defined as the Cartesian product of integer extents, [0..N0) X
[0..N1) X [0..N2) ...

Implementation from https://github.com/kokkos/mdspan. This provides backports
for C++14, 17, and 20.

